{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775893033334,"sessionID":"ses_2848c743dffeBSEEKFJu9e5mea","part":{"id":"prt_d7b75708d001S4f9ZdTR2XEucL","messageID":"msg_d7b747aed001fwoEftB9ICbUJw","sessionID":"ses_2848c743dffeBSEEKFJu9e5mea","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_a8bada90bd95424cb32d6b4a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-040: Python SDK/CLI 单元测试 — Design\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Purpose\n\nThis AR covers comprehensive Python unit tests for the `agentcube-sdk` package (`sdk-python/`). The SDK provides high-level Python clients for creating Code Interpreter sessions via the Workload Manager (control plane) and executing code/files via the Router (data plane), plus invoking AgentRuntime workloads.\n\n### 1.2 Scope\n\n| Module | File | Lines | Test File | Status |\n|--------|------|-------|-----------|--------|\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | `CodeInterpreterClient` | 161 | `tests/test_code_interpreter.py` | **Partial** — 635 lines, but 3 methods missing `test_` prefix (won't run) |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | `AgentRuntimeClient` | 79 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** — 837 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | `ControlPlaneClient` | 96 | `tests/test_control_plane.py` | **Good** — 370 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | 176 | `tests/test_data_plane.py` | **Good** — 641 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | 80 | `tests/test_agent_runtime.py` | **Good** |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Exception classes | 21 | `tests/test_exceptions.py` | **Good** — 77 lines |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session` | 14 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Good** |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file` | 7 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Partial** — missing edge cases |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger` | 17 | `tests/test_utils.py` | **Partial** — missing handler reuse test |\n| `agentcube/__init__.py` | Public exports | 5 | `tests/test_imports.py` | **Good** — 55 lines |\n| `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` | Client re-exports | 6 | `tests/test_imports.py` | **Good** |\n\n### 1.3 System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        Python SDK (agentcube)                        │\n│                                                                       │\n│  ┌──────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────────────┐     │\n│  │  CodeInterpreterClient│     │     AgentRuntimeClient        │     │\n│  │  (high-level facade)  │     │   (high-level facade)         │     │\n│  └───────┬──────────────┘     └──────────┬────────────────────┘     │\n│          │                               │                           │\n│  ┌───────▼──────────────┐     ┌──────────▼────────────────────┐     │\n│  │  ControlPlaneClient  │     │  AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient  │     │\n│  │  (Workload Manager)  │     │   (Router — Agent Runtime)    │     │\n│  └──────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────────────┘     │\n│          │                                                       │\n│  ┌───────▼──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │           CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient                      │  │\n│  │              (Router — Code Interpreter)                      │  │\n│  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│                                                                       │\n│  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                    Utilities                                   │  │\n│  │  create_session  │  read_token_from_file  │  get_logger       │  │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n│  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                   Exceptions                                   │  │\n│  │  AgentCubeError → CommandExecutionError                       │  │\n│  │                 → SessionError                                │  │\n│  │                 → DataPlaneError                              │  │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n         │                                              │\n         ▼                                              ▼\n┌──────────────────┐                        ┌──────────────────────┐\n│  Workload Manager│                        │      Router           │\n│  (Control Plane) │                        │  (Data Plane)         │\n│  K8s API Server  │                        │  HTTP proxy to pods   │\n└──────────────────┘                        └──────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.4 Design Principles\n\n- **Mock at the boundary**: All HTTP calls are mocked via `MagicMock` on `session.post/get/delete/request`. No real network calls.\n- **`unittest.mock.patch`**: Used for class-level and function-level patching. Consistent with existing test patterns.\n- **Environment isolation**: Tests that depend on env vars use `patch.dict(os.environ, ...)` with `clear=True`.\n- **Resource cleanup**: Every test that creates a client calls `client.close()` or `client.stop()` to release HTTP sessions.\n- **Table-driven patterns**: Where applicable (e.g., language aliases, timeout variants), use parameterized approaches.\n\n### 1.5 Package Structure (test files)\n\n```\npython-sdk/tests/\n├── __init__.py                          # Package marker\n├── conftest.py                          # Shared fixtures (mock_requests_session, mock_create_session)\n├── test_imports.py                      # Package import and __all__ verification\n├── test_exceptions.py                   # Exception hierarchy tests\n├── test_utils.py                        # Utility function tests (http, utils, log)\n├── test_control_plane.py                # ControlPlaneClient tests\n├── test_data_plane.py                   # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient tests\n├── test_code_interpreter.py             # CodeInterpreterClient tests\n├── test_agent_runtime.py                # AgentRuntimeClient + AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient tests\n└── test_integration.py                  # NEW — cross-component integration tests\n```\n\n### 1.6 Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Test Use |\n|------------|---------|----------|\n| `pytest` | ≥8.0 | Test runner, fixtures, parametrize |\n| `requests` | any | HTTP client (mocked) |\n| `PyJWT` | ≥2.0.0 | SDK dependency (not directly tested) |\n| `cryptography` | any | SDK dependency (not directly tested) |\n| `unittest.mock` | stdlib | MagicMock, patch, patch.dict |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Data Structures\n\n### 2.1 Mock Objects Required\n\n#### `mock_http_response` (requests.Response)\n\nStandard mock for HTTP responses across all client tests:\n\n```python\nmock_resp = MagicMock(spec=requests.Response)\nmock_resp.json.return_value = {\"sessionId\": \"abc-123\"}\nmock_resp.status_code = 200\nmock_resp.raise_for_status = MagicMock()\nmock_resp.headers = {\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"session-1\"}\nmock_resp.iter_content.return_value = [b\"chunk1\", b\"chunk2\"]\n```\n\n#### `mock_session` (requests.Session)\n\nUsed when testing session-level behavior:\n\n```python\nmock_session = MagicMock()\nmock_session.post.return_value = mock_resp\nmock_session.get.return_value = mock_resp\nmock_session.delete.return_value = mock_resp\nmock_session.request.return_value = mock_resp\nmock_session.headers = {}\nmock_session.adapters = {\"http://\": adapter, \"https://\": adapter}\n```\n\n### 2.2 Test Fixtures\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient fixture\n\n```python\ndef make_ci_client(session_id=\"sess-1\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\", **kwargs):\n    \"\"\"Create a CodeInterpreterClient with mocked dependencies.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.ControlPlaneClient\") as mock_cp, \\\n         patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_cp.return_value = MagicMock()\n        mock_dp.return_value = MagicMock()\n        client = CodeInterpreterClient(session_id=session_id, router_url=router_url, **kwargs)\n        yield client, mock_cp, mock_dp\n        client.stop()\n```\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient fixture\n\n```python\ndef make_ar_client(session_id=\"sess-1\", router_url=\"http://router:8080\", **kwargs):\n    \"\"\"Create an AgentRuntimeClient with mocked dependencies.\"\"\"\n    with patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\") as mock_dp:\n        mock_dp.return_value = MagicMock()\n        mock_dp.return_value.bootstrap_session_id.return_value = session_id\n        client = AgentRuntimeClient(agent_name=\"test-agent\", router_url=router_url, **kwargs)\n        yield client, mock_dp\n        client.close()\n```\n\n### 2.2 Key Class Signatures\n\n#### CodeInterpreterClient\n\n| Method | Signature | Delegates To |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `__init__` | `(name, namespace, ttl, workload_manager_url, router_url, auth_token, verbose, session_id)` | ControlPlaneClient + CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient |\n| `_init_data_plane` | `() -> None` | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient(session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name) |\n| `__enter__` | `() -> self` | — |\n| `__exit__` | `(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None` | `stop()` |\n| `stop` | `() -> None` | dp_client.close(), cp_client.delete_session(), cp_client.close() |\n| `execute_command` | `(command: str, timeout: Optional[float]) -> str` | dp_client.execute_command([command], timeout+2.0) |\n| `run_code` | `(language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float]) -> str` | write_file() + execute_command() |\n| `write_file` | `(content: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | dp_client.write_file() |\n| `upload_file` | `(local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None` | dp_client.upload_file() |\n| `download_file` | `(remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None` | dp_client.download_file() |\n| `list_files` | `(path: str=\".\") -> Any` | dp_client.list_files() |\n\n#### ControlPlaneClient\n\n| Method | Signature | HTTP |\n|--------|-----------|------|\n| `__init__` | `(workload_manager_url, auth_token, timeout, connect_timeout, pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` | Creates session with headers |\n| `create_session` | `(name, namespace, metadata, ttl) -> str` | POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` |\n| `delete_session` | `(session_id: str) -> bool` | DELETE `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{id}` |\n| `close` | `() -> None` | session.close() |\n\n#### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n| Method | Signature | HTTP |\n|--------|-----------|------|\n| `__init__` | `(session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name, base_url, timeout, connect_timeout, pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` | Creates session with `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n| `_request` | `(method, endpoint, body, **kwargs) -> Response` | `{base_url}{endpoint}` |\n| `execute_command` | `(command: Union[str, List], timeout: Optional[float]) -> str` | POST `api/execute` |\n| `run_code` | `(language, code, timeout) -> str` | write_file + execute_command |\n| `write_file` | `(content, remote_path) -> None` | POST `api/files` (JSON, base64) |\n| `upload_file` | `(local_path, remote_path) -> None` | POST `api/files` (multipart) |\n| `download_file` | `(remote_path, local_path) -> None` | GET `api/files/{clean_path}` (stream) |\n| `list_files` | `(path=\".\") -> Any` | GET `api/files?path={path}` |\n| `close` | `() -> None` | session.close() |\n\n#### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n| Method | Signature | HTTP |\n|--------|-----------|------|\n| `__init__` | `(router_url, namespace, agent_name, timeout, connect_timeout, pool_connections, pool_maxsize)` | Creates session |\n| `bootstrap_session_id` | `() -> str` | GET `{base_url}` → reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header |\n| `invoke` | `(session_id, payload, timeout) -> Response` | POST `{base_url}` with JSON + session header |\n| `close` | `() -> None` | session.close() |\n\n#### AgentRuntimeClient\n\n| Method | Signature | Delegates To |\n|--------|-----------|-------------|\n| `__init__` | `(agent_name, namespace, router_url, verbose, session_id, timeout, connect_timeout)` | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient + bootstrap |\n| `__enter__` | `() -> self` | — |\n| `__exit__` | `(exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None` | `close()` |\n| `invoke` | `(payload: Dict, timeout: Optional[float]) -> Any` | dp_client.invoke() → resp.json() |\n| `close` | `() -> None` | dp_client.close() |\n\n---\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 CodeInterpreterClient Contracts\n\n#### Initialization\n\n| Scenario | Condition | Result |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| No session_id provided | `session_id=None` | Calls `cp_client.create_session()`, sets `self.session_id`, sets `_session_created=True` |\n| Session_id provided | `session_id=\"existing\"` | Skips create_session, sets `_session_created=False` |\n| Router URL from arg | `router_url=\"http://x\"` | Uses provided URL |\n| Router URL from env | `router_url=None`, `ROUTER_URL=\"http://x\"` | Uses env var |\n| Router URL missing | Neither arg nor env | Raises `ValueError(\"router_url must be provided or ROUTER_URL env var must be set\")` |\n\n#### Data Plane Init Failure\n\n| Scenario | `_session_created` | `session_id` | Result |\n|----------|-------------------|-------------|--------|\n| DP init fails, session was created | True | non-None | Logs warning, calls `delete_session(session_id)`, sets `session_id=None`, re-raises |\n| DP init fails, session was reused | False | non-None | Re-raises without cleanup (caller owns session) |\n\n#### Context Manager\n\n| Scenario | Result |\n|----------|--------|\n| `__enter__` | Returns `self` |\n| `__exit__` (no exception) | Calls `stop()` |\n| `__exit__` (with exception) | Calls `stop()`, returns `None` (does not suppress) |\n\n#### stop()\n\n| Condition | Action |\n|-----------|--------|\n| `dp_client` exists and not None | `dp_client.close()`, set to `None` |\n| `session_id` is not None | `cp_client.delete_session(session_id)`, set to `None` |\n| `cp_client` exists and not None | `cp_client.close()`, set to `None` |\n| Called multiple times | Idempotent — no-op after first call |\n\n#### execute_command\n\n| Input | Transformation | DP Call |\n|-------|---------------|---------|\n| `\"echo hello\"` (string) | → `[\"echo hello\"]` | `dp.execute_command([\"echo hello\"], timeout=read_timeout)` |\n| `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (list) | → `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (as-is) | `dp.execute_command([\"ls\", \"-la\"], timeout=read_timeout)` |\n| `timeout=None` | → `timeout_value=120`, `read_timeout=122.0` | DP call with `(connect_timeout, 122.0)` |\n| `timeout=10.0` | → `timeout_value=10.0`, `read_timeout=12.0` | DP call with `(connect_timeout, 12.0)` |\n\n#### run_code\n\n| Language | Action |\n|----------|--------|\n| `\"python\"`, `\"py\"`, `\"python3\"` (case-insensitive) | Write timestamped `.py` file, execute `python3 <file>` |\n| Any other | Raises `ValueError(\"Unsupported language: {language}\")` |\n\n### 3.2 ControlPlaneClient Contracts\n\n#### Initialization\n\n| Condition | Result |\n|-----------|--------|\n| `workload_manager_url` provided | `base_url = workload_manager_url` |\n| `workload_manager_url=None`, env set | `base_url = WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` |\n| Neither provided | Raises `ValueError(\"workload_manager_url must be provided or WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var must be set\")` |\n| `auth_token` provided | `Authorization: Bearer {token}` header set |\n| `auth_token=None`, SA file exists | Token read from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n| `auth_token=None`, SA file missing | No Authorization header set |\n| `auth_token=\"\"` (empty string) | No Authorization header set (falsy check) |\n\n#### create_session\n\n| HTTP | Request | Response |\n|------|---------|----------|\n| POST `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON: `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` | Returns `data[\"sessionId\"]` |\n| Timeout | `(connect_timeout, timeout)` | — |\n| Missing sessionId in response | — | Raises `ValueError(\"Response missing 'sessionId' field\")` |\n| HTTP error | — | `resp.raise_for_status()` propagates |\n\n#### delete_session\n\n| HTTP Status | Result |\n|-------------|--------|\n| 2xx | Returns `True` |\n| 404 | Returns `True` (idempotent) |\n| Other error (HTTPError, ConnectionError, Timeout) | Logs warning, returns `False` |\n\n### 3.3 CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient Contracts\n\n#### Base URL Construction\n\n| Condition | Result |\n|-----------|--------|\n| `base_url` provided | `self.base_url = base_url` (ignores router_url/namespace/cr_name) |\n| `base_url=None` | `self.base_url = urljoin(router_url, \"/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\")` |\n\n#### execute_command\n\n| Input | Body | Timeout |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `\"sleep 10\"`, `timeout=10.0` | `{\"command\": [\"sleep\", \"10\"], \"timeout\": \"10s\"}` | `(connect_timeout, 12.0)` |\n| `\"ls\"`, `timeout=None` | `{\"command\": [\"ls\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` | `(connect_timeout, 122.0)` |\n| `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` (list) | `{\"command\": [\"ls\", \"-la\"], \"timeout\": \"120s\"}` | `(connect_timeout, 122.0)` |\n\n| Response | Result |\n|----------|--------|\n| `{\"exit_code\": 0, \"stdout\": \"ok\"}` | Returns `\"ok\"` |\n| `{\"exit_code\": 1, \"stderr\": \"err\"}` | Raises `CommandExecutionError(exit_code=1, stderr=\"err\", command=[...])` |\n\n#### write_file\n\n| Input | Body |\n|-------|------|\n| `\"hello\"`, `/tmp/test.txt` | `{\"path\": \"/tmp/test.txt\", \"content\": base64(\"hello\"), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n\n#### upload_file\n\n| Input | Multipart |\n|-------|-----------|\n| `/local/file.txt`, `/remote/file.txt` | `files={'file': ('file.txt', f)}`, `data={'path': '/remote/file.txt', 'mode': '0644'}`, headers include `x-agentcube-session-id` |\n\n#### download_file\n\n| Input | URL |\n|-------|-----|\n| `/remote/path.txt`, `/local/out.txt` | GET `{base_url}api/files/remote/path.txt` (leading `/` stripped) |\n\n### 3.4 AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient Contracts\n\n#### bootstrap_session_id\n\n| Response Header | Result |\n|-----------------|--------|\n| `x-agentcube-session-id: abc-123` | Returns `\"abc-123\"` |\n| Missing header | Raises `ValueError(\"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\")` |\n| HTTP error | `raise_for_status()` propagates |\n\n#### invoke\n\n| Input | Headers | Timeout |\n|-------|---------|---------|\n| `session_id=\"s1\"`, `payload={}`, `timeout=None` | `{\"x-agentcube-session-id\": \"s1\", \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}` | `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` |\n| `timeout=30.0` | Same | `(connect_timeout, 30.0)` |\n\n### 3.5 Utility Contracts\n\n#### create_session\n\n| Input | Result |\n|-------|--------|\n| `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` (defaults) | Session with HTTPAdapter mounted on `http://` and `https://` |\n| Custom values | Session with custom pool settings |\n\n#### read_token_from_file\n\n| Condition | Result |\n|-----------|--------|\n| File exists with `\"token\\n\"` | Returns `\"token\"` (stripped) |\n| File exists with `\"  token  \\n\"` | Returns `\"token\"` (stripped) |\n| File not found | Returns `\"\"` |\n\n#### get_logger\n\n| Condition | Result |\n|-----------|--------|\n| First call with name `\"x\"` | Creates logger, adds StreamHandler with formatter |\n| Second call with same name `\"x\"` | Returns existing logger (no duplicate handlers) |\n| `level=logging.DEBUG` | Logger level = 10 |\n| `level=\"DEBUG\"` | Logger level = 10 |\n| `level=logging.INFO` (default) | Logger level = 20 |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Error Classification\n\n| Component | Error Source | Test Strategy |\n|-----------|-------------|---------------|\n| ControlPlaneClient | `create_session` HTTP error | Mock `session.post` with `raise_for_status` side_effect |\n| ControlPlaneClient | `delete_session` network error | Mock `session.delete` with `RequestException` side_effect |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | `execute_command` non-zero exit | Mock response JSON with `exit_code != 0` |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | Any HTTP error | Mock `session.request` with `raise_for_status` side_effect |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `bootstrap_session_id` missing header | Mock response with empty headers dict |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `invoke` HTTP error | Mock `session.post` with `raise_for_status` side_effect |\n| CodeInterpreterClient | DP init failure | Mock `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` constructor to raise |\n| CodeInterpreterClient | Router URL missing | Patch env, assert `ValueError` |\n| AgentRuntimeClient | Session not initialized | Mock bootstrap to return `None` or `\"\"` |\n\n### 4.2 Exception Hierarchy\n\n```\nException\n└── AgentCubeError (base)\n    ├── CommandExecutionError (exit_code, stderr, command)\n    ├── SessionError (docstring only, not raised by core)\n    └── DataPlaneError (docstring only, not raised by core)\n```\n\nTests verify:\n- `issubclass(CommandExecutionError, AgentCubeError)` → True\n- `issubclass(SessionError, AgentCubeError)` → True\n- `issubclass(DataPlaneError, AgentCubeError)` → True\n- `CommandExecutionError` attributes: `exit_code`, `stderr`, `command`\n- `CommandExecutionError` message format: `\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\"`\n\n---\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Test Categories\n\n| Category | Scope | Files |\n|----------|-------|-------|\n| Import/export tests | Package structure, `__all__` | `test_imports.py` |\n| Exception tests | Hierarchy, attributes, messages | `test_exceptions.py` |\n| Utility tests | Pure functions, no side effects | `test_utils.py` |\n| Control plane tests | HTTP client, session lifecycle | `test_control_plane.py` |\n| Data plane tests (CI) | HTTP client, file ops, execute | `test_data_plane.py` |\n| Data plane tests (AR) | HTTP client, bootstrap, invoke | `test_agent_runtime.py` |\n| High-level CI client | Facade, lifecycle, delegation | `test_code_interpreter.py` |\n| High-level AR client | Facade, lifecycle, delegation | `test_agent_runtime.py` |\n| Integration tests | Cross-component, end-to-end flows | `test_integration.py` (NEW) |\n\n### 5.2 Bug Fixes Required (Existing Tests)\n\n#### `test_code_interpreter.py` — Missing `test_` prefix\n\nThree methods in `TestStop` class are named without `test_` prefix and will NOT be discovered by pytest:\n\n| Current Name | Required Name |\n|--------------|---------------|\n| `stop_closes_dp_client` | `test_stop_closes_dp_client` |\n| `stop_deletes_session` | `test_stop_deletes_session` |\n| `stop_closes_cp_client` | `test_stop_closes_cp_client` |\n\n### 5.3 Detailed Test Plan — New/Additional Tests\n\n#### `test_code_interpreter.py` — Additional Tests\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `test_stop_when_session_id_is_none` | stop | session_id=None → skips delete_session, still closes dp and cp |\n| 2 | `test_stop_when_dp_client_not_initialized` | stop | No dp_client attribute → no crash (hasattr check) |\n| 3 | `test_stop_when_cp_client_not_initialized` | stop | No cp_client attribute → no crash (hasattr check) |\n| 4 | `test_run_code_python3_language` | run_code | `\"python3\"` → writes file + executes |\n| 5 | `test_run_code_py_language` | run_code | `\"py\"` → writes file + executes |\n| 6 | `test_run_code_case_insensitive` | run_code | `\"PYTHON\"` → writes file + executes |\n| 7 | `test_run_code_passes_timeout_to_execute` | run_code | `timeout=30.0` → passed through to execute_command |\n| 8 | `test_execute_command_with_list_input` | execute_command | `[\"ls\", \"-la\"]` → passed as-is to dp (not double-wrapped) |\n| 9 | `test_execute_command_empty_string` | execute_command | `\"\"` → `[\"\"]` sent to dp |\n| 10 | `test_session_created_flag_true_when_no_session_id` | __init__ | `_session_created=True` when session_id=None |\n| 11 | `test_session_created_flag_false_when_session_id_provided` | __init__ | `_session_created=False` when session_id provided |\n| 12 | `test_logger_name_is_correct` | __init__ | `logger.name == \"agentcube.code_interpreter\"` |\n| 13 | `test_data_plane_init_called_with_correct_params` | _init_data_plane | session_id, router_url, namespace, cr_name passed correctly |\n\n#### `test_data_plane.py` — Additional Tests\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `test_execute_command_http_error_propagates` | execute_command | HTTP 500 → raise_for_status propagates HTTPError |\n| 2 | `test_write_file_http_error_propagates` | write_file | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n| 3 | `test_write_file_unicode_content` | write_file | Unicode string → base64 encoded correctly |\n| 4 | `test_upload_file_nonexistent_raises_io_error` | upload_file | File not found → FileNotFoundError propagates |\n| 5 | `test_upload_file_http_error_propagates` | upload_file | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n| 6 | `test_download_file_creates_local_file` | download_file | Verifies file content written correctly |\n| 7 | `test_list_files_http_error_propagates` | list_files | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n| 8 | `test_run_code_delegates_to_write_and_execute` | run_code | Full delegation path verified |\n| 9 | `test_request_default_timeout_tuple` | _request | No timeout override → `(connect_timeout, self.timeout)` |\n| 10 | `test_request_custom_timeout_override` | _request | timeout kwarg → used instead of default |\n\n#### `test_control_plane.py` — Additional Tests\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `test_create_session_with_none_metadata` | create_session | `metadata=None` → body includes `\"metadata\": null` |\n| 2 | `test_create_session_url_with_trailing_slash` | create_session | base_url with trailing slash → URL constructed correctly |\n| 3 | `test_delete_session_url_construction` | delete_session | Verifies exact URL format |\n| 4 | `test_session_headers_content_type_always_set` | __init__ | Content-Type always `application/json` |\n| 5 | `test_auth_token_empty_string_no_header` | __init__ | `auth_token=\"\"` → no Authorization header |\n\n#### `test_agent_runtime.py` — Additional Tests\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `test_invoke_http_error_propagates` | invoke (DP) | HTTP error → raise_for_status propagates |\n| 2 | `test_invoke_with_empty_payload` | invoke (DP) | `{}` → valid POST |\n| 3 | `test_bootstrap_session_id_empty_string_treated_as_missing` | bootstrap_session_id | Header value `\"\"` → raises ValueError |\n| 4 | `test_close_delegates_to_session_close` | close (DP) | Verifies session.close() called |\n\n#### `test_utils.py` — Additional Tests\n\n| # | Test Name | Function | Description |\n|---|-----------|----------|-------------|\n| 1 | `test_read_token_from_file_empty_file` | read_token_from_file | Empty file → returns `\"\"` |\n| 2 | `test_read_token_from_file_multiline_strips` | read_token_from_file | `\"token\\n\\n\"` → returns `\"token\"` |\n| 3 | `test_get_logger_handler_not_duplicated` | get_logger | Second call with same name → only 1 handler |\n| 4 | `test_get_logger_formatter_is_set` | get_logger | Handler has Formatter with correct format string |\n| 5 | `test_get_logger_handler_is_stream_handler` | get_logger | Handler type is StreamHandler |\n| 6 | `test_create_session_independent_instances` | create_session | Two calls → two independent Session objects |\n\n#### `test_integration.py` — NEW File\n\n| # | Test Name | Components | Description |\n|---|-----------|------------|-------------|\n| 1 | `test_ci_full_lifecycle_create_execute_stop` | CI Client + CP + DP | Create session → execute command → stop (full flow with all mocks) |\n| 2 | `test_ci_context_manager_with_exception` | CI Client + CP + DP | Exception in context block → stop still called |\n| 3 | `test_ci_pre_provisioned_session_no_control_plane_calls` | CI Client + CP | session_id provided → no create_session call |\n| 4 | `test_ci_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup` | CI Client + CP + DP | DP init fails → session deleted, exception re-raised |\n| 5 | `test_ar_full_lifecycle_bootstrap_invoke_close` | AR Client + DP | Bootstrap session → invoke → close (full flow) |\n| 6 | `test_ar_context_manager_with_exception` | AR Client + DP | Exception in context block → close still called |\n| 7 | `test_ar_pre_provisioned_session_no_bootstrap` | AR Client + DP | session_id provided → no bootstrap call |\n| 8 | `test_ar_missing_session_id_invoke_raises` | AR Client + DP | Bootstrap returns None → invoke raises ValueError |\n| 9 | `test_ci_execute_command_timeout_propagation` | CI Client + DP | Custom timeout → +2.0 buffer → DP receives correct value |\n| 10 | `test_ar_invoke_timeout_propagation` | AR Client + DP | Custom timeout → DP receives correct value |\n| 11 | `test_ci_run_code_python_writes_and_executes` | CI Client + DP | run_code(\"python\", ...) → write_file + execute_command |\n| 12 | `test_ci_run_code_unsupported_language` | CI Client | run_code(\"ruby\", ...) → ValueError |\n| 13 | `test_ci_file_operations_delegation` | CI Client + DP | write/upload/download/list all delegate to DP |\n| 14 | `test_cp_create_and_delete_session_flow` | CP Client | create_session → delete_session → verify URLs and methods |\n| 15 | `test_dp_execute_command_exit_code_error` | CI DP Client | Non-zero exit → CommandExecutionError raised |\n| 16 | `test_env_var_precedence_router_url` | CI Client | Arg takes precedence over ROUTER_URL env var |\n| 17 | `test_env_var_precedence_workload_manager_url` | CP Client | Arg takes precedence over WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL env var |\n| 18 | `test_ci_stop_idempotent` | CI Client | Multiple stop() calls → each cleanup action called exactly once |\n| 19 | `test_ar_close_idempotent` | AR Client | Multiple close() calls → dp_client.close called each time |\n| 20 | `test_ci_session_created_flag_behavior` | CI Client | _session_created=True → cleanup on DP failure; False → no cleanup |\n\n### 5.4 Mocking Strategy\n\n| Dependency | Mock Approach | Rationale |\n|-----------|---------------|-----------|\n| `ControlPlaneClient` | `patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.ControlPlaneClient\")` | Isolates CI client from control plane |\n| `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` | `patch(\"agentcube.code_interpreter.CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\")` | Isolates CI client from data plane |\n| `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` | `patch(\"agentcube.agent_runtime.AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\")` | Isolates AR client from data plane |\n| `requests.Session` methods | `client.session.post = MagicMock(...)` | Direct method replacement on session instance |\n| `read_token_from_file` | `patch(\"agentcube.clients.control_plane.read_token_from_file\")` | Avoids filesystem dependency |\n| `os.environ` | `patch.dict(os.environ, {...}, clear=True)` | Environment isolation |\n| `SA_TOKEN_PATH` | `patch(\"agentcube.clients.control_plane.SA_TOKEN_PATH\", \"/tmp/token\")` | Redirect SA token path |\n\n### 5.5 Test Execution\n\n```bash\n# Run all Python SDK tests\ncd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/ -v\n\n# Run with coverage\ncd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/ -v --cov=agentcube --cov-report=term-missing\n\n# Run specific test file\ncd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py -v\n\n# Run specific test class\ncd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/test_code_interpreter.py::TestStop -v\n\n# Run only the newly added tests (by keyword)\ncd python-sdk && python -m pytest tests/ -v -k \"test_stop_when_session\"\n```\n\n### 5.6 Coverage Targets\n\n| Module | Current (est.) | Target |\n|--------|---------------|--------|\n| `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | ~75% (3 stop tests not running) | >95% |\n| `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | ~90% | >95% |\n| `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | ~85% | >95% |\n| `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | ~85% | >95% |\n| `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | ~85% | >95% |\n| `agentcube/exceptions.py` | ~95% | 100% |\n| `agentcube/utils/http.py` | ~90% | 100% |\n| `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | ~80% | 100% |\n| `agentcube/utils/log.py` | ~70% | >90% |\n| **Overall** | ~82% | >92% |\n\n### 5.7 Risk Areas\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|-----------|\n| `stop()` methods missing `test_` prefix | Fix immediately — 3 tests silently skipped |\n| `close()` idempotency on `requests.Session` | `Session.close()` is safe to call multiple times; tests verify call count |\n| Environment variable leakage between tests | Use `patch.dict(os.environ, ..., clear=True)` consistently |\n| Logger handler duplication across tests | `get_logger` checks `if not logger.handlers`; test verifies this |\n| Base64 encoding edge cases (empty, unicode) | Test with `\"\"`, unicode strings, binary-like content |\n| Timeout buffer logic (`+2.0`) | Test with various timeout values to verify buffer applied correctly |\n| `urljoin` behavior with trailing slashes | Test both with and without trailing slash on router_url |\n\n### 5.8 CI Integration\n\nThe existing CI workflow (`.github/workflows/python-sdk-tests.yml`) runs:\n```yaml\npython -m pytest tests/ -v\n```\n\nNo changes needed to CI config. New tests will be picked up automatically by pytest discovery.\n\nLint workflow (`.github/workflows/python-lint.yml`) uses `ruff` — ensure new test files pass lint:\n```bash\npython3 -m ruff check python-sdk/tests/ --config pyproject.toml\n```\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/agentcube/code_interpreter.py\">\nERROR [161:31] \"list_files\" is not a known attribute of \"None